@Happypig375 you can do:

```c#
XmlReader reader = XmlReader.Create(new StringReader(someSvgString));

var svg = new SKSvg();
svg.Load(reader);
```

@Happypig375 You can use the default. You can pass in a stream of your xml content. That will load with the settings from SkSvg

``` csharp
string svgText = @"<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='24' height='24' viewBox='0 0 24 24'><path d='M0 0h24v24H0z' fill='none'/><path d='M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z' fill='#ffffff'/></svg>";
byte[] bytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(svgText);
MemoryStream stream = new MemoryStream(bytes);
SKSvg svg = new SKSvg();
svg.Load(stream);
```

``` csharp
public SKPicture Load(Stream stream)
{
      using (XmlReader reader = XmlReader.Create(stream, this.xmlReaderSettings, SKSvg.CreateSvgXmlContext()))
        return this.Load(reader);
}
```
